ution within the\n{\\sigma} and {\\pi} channels of adsorbates. Finally, we also present oxygen\nadsorption and oxygen vacancy formation energies in these oxide systems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 20 Dec 2014 03:00:50 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 21 Mar 2015 18:50:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-23"}
